			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">OMG Bards are POWERFUL in LDoN!<a name="12858"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 5 03 12:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have always agreed that LDoN was made with bards in mind, but after last night, I think even more highly of what bards can do (and that's a tall order coming from a devout bard like me). Note, not tooting my own horn (pun intended) here.
<br />

<br />
Aryon, my cleric buddy sends me a tell asking if I want an LDoN group.  Normally I always follow that up with what classes you got to make sure they don't have a non-chealing druid as main healer.  For Aryon, it's an immediate sure.
<br />

<br />
I get there without asking what we have, only to find out we have a 65 Cleric, 65 Pally MA, 59 War, 63 Rogue, 62 Mage, and me a 62 Bard.  Notice anything about that group?  Actually took me a second myself, but I soon came to realize we had no slow, no haste, and no CC for LDoN...  Now I'm a fair bard and know my class as well as most, but come on... Haste (dependent), Slow (pre 64 bards aren't much in the way of slowers), Snare, CC, Pulling, mana and DS is a tall order for one person, hehe!  I was busier than I've ever been in my bard career, reminded me of learning to swarm kite.  
<br />

<br />
Well, to make a long story short, we did surprisingly well!  We didn't win due to stingy mobs (collection where we got all but 3 in 30 min. and couldn't get the last one before time ran out).  But we would have if it weren't for a hellish room FILLED with mobs close together and filled with spiderwebs.  I hate spiderwebs, you can't target through them worth a darn.  Well, needless to say trying to target and lull up close caused a train of about 4 mobs that resisted 7 out of 8 attempts to mez.  After the wipe, we raced to get V back (the only buff we had other than the mage's DS) on the MA and pull one last mob.  Halfway through the mob, the time expired but 20 seconds later we got partial points. GRRRR.  
<br />

<br />
<b>Essentially though, it was a testament to just how awesome a bard can be when they use every skill and song they have to their potential!</b>
<br />

<br />
One other note, I found out that if you are VERY careful, you can actually use Mischief in LDoN to slow 45%, which is not too shabby for us folks without Requium of Time.  One time I accidently triggered a trap (bitten victim) but the few spiders that spawned were easy to mez and dispatch.  I combination of Assonance (32% slow) for areas where a trap or adds may be aggro'd with AoE slow, and AoE slow (45%) worked out well.  I just sent a tell to the cleric anytime I was using the lower slow, but with our DPS, it didn't use up that much more mana with our quick battles.  I will definitely keep this slow strategy in the back of my mind if I'm ever the main slower again.  Just remember, Mischief has a dot component so if you do aggro something with it, you have to wait until it wears off (18 seconds) to mez it or mez will be broken.
<br />

<br />
All in all, I had a blast, but was busier than a one-armed paper hanger for an hour.  Even though we didn't win, we should have (I had just finished a collection in 28 min. with a standard group and this wierd group had 3 left after 30 min.).  I think the folks that were there have a new respect for bards, which was worth it to me.  Hehe. 
<br />

<br />
BARDS RAWK!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
