				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: OMG Bards are POWERFUL in LDoN!<a name="12864"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 5 03 1:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hmm edit didn't seem to work.  Go figure.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I thought about it and decided to add my playlist for you in case it helps.  
<br />

<br />
1) 62-Zek (As sole haster, this was a must)
<br />
2) 60-Warsong (Overhaste is always in my twist)
<br />
3) 62-Mischief (45% Slow and 35 pt. dot used most of the time)
<br />
4) 62-Marr (Would twist in at 50% and 10% health)
<br />
5) 60-Assonance (Pull song, 32% slow and 45 pt. dot, if tight quarters and AoE not possible, this was only slow, otherwise it made for a nice 80 pt. dot when combined with Mischief)
<br />
6) 61-Quellious (Lull)
<br />
7) 62-Thule (Mez)
<br />
8) 51-Largos (rarely did I need to snare but when I did it saved adds)
<br />

<br />
Hehe I can't stress enough the recommendation to STUDY the songlist, you never know when you will be called on to do the impossible, something bards CAN do if they use their songs and skills to the fullest advantage.  RAWK ON!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
