				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: OMG Bards are POWERFUL in LDoN!<a name="12874"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 5 03 3:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've had less than a great deal of experience with Tak, but what I do on all doors is click it open from the farthest distance I can and back up, then move sideways outside the room to see if I can target a door guard or two.  I have had a great deal of success there, even if I have to move in to lull, I just pop in, cast, back out. Seems I'm not in their aggro range long enough to aggro before lull hits then I can camp them pretty much.  You are right, I have never used my SS helm because I find prescious time is wasted (poor choice of words) on lulling every mob in the room before I pull the closest just to avoid adds.  Even at 3 seconds a lull, it can take forever to clear a room with 8 mobs in it.  
<br />

<br />
Once in a while I get aggro on one mob of a 2 guard door, but normally I've lulled the next closest and one of the door guards so I only get one mob and it's no big deal.  I don't remember if Tak is special, but I've had great success pulling in LDoN.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
