				<td colspan="2"><span>So far my LDoN experience has been pretty wild.  Some groups just want me to train the entire room and off tank, others want me to help mez and others don't have a clue what I'm capable of doing or what they're doing<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Anyhow, just thought I'd throw my two cents in regarding a few things.  Your song list is pretty well thought out there Sin, just wanted to add my normal line up as another option:
<br />

<br />
1. Zek (haste, atk, str)
<br />
2. Psalm of Warmth (ds)
<br />
3. Warsong (overhaste<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
4. Largo's or Marr
<br />
5. OOS (great for pulling)
<br />
6. Mez
<br />
7. Quellious
<br />

<br />
What I typically do when pulling is get the room lulled, pick my target, start OOS and run back next to the main tank.  The nice thing about this is OOS has a HUGE range so by the time it actually hits the mob I can have zek and psalm going which means when the mob hits me it's eating my DS<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
As for those doors in Tak I guess I've been pretty lucky as they don't seem to cause me much grief other than they will close on me every so often while I'm trying to target.  On the other hand, even if I am the main cc I don't mind getting an add or two since I can get a couple of songs in for the group while keeping mez up.  The trick here is to have an /assist hotkey.  Taking my song line up above, and assuming I'm the main slower, my typical twist with one add would be 1, 3, /assist, 4, target mob to mez, 6.  This allows me to keep the group fairly well buffed, the main mob slowed and the add mezzed.  It gets a little bit worse with more than one add, and if there's enough tankage I'll just ask for them to tank mez since that's going to be faster in some cases than me trying to keep mez on 3 or 4 mobs.
<br />

<br />
Happy adventuring and may your voice never give out<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
