				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: OMG Bards are POWERFUL in LDoN!<a name="12992"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 8 03 4:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><b>Sinfonian</b>
<br />

<br />
Here are a few other things I thought of in relation to toggle:
<br />
1) Make sure your options window under keyboard has TAB set as Toggle Last Two Targets (I think that's the name of the function) and nothing else.
<br />

<br />
2) As a note, the &quot;Toggle Last Two Targets&quot; function didn't always work this way, at least not for me.  Before an update that occurred during the PoP Era, I remember using a much more elaborate keyset that involved targeting a mob and then targeting self (F1 for most; I remapped it to g) to &quot;save&quot; that target to the TAB key.  When I wanted to recall it later, I would hit ESC to clear my current target, then I would target self and hit TAB, and this would recall my target.  Under this old system, just hitting TAB would cause me to switch back and forth between targeting whatever I was targeting at the moment and targeting myself (even if self was not my previous target).
<br />

<br />
Under the new system, the trick I described above seems to have stopped working, and it has been replaced by the much more obvious method of &quot;hit the TAB key and it will swap between your current target and whatever you were targeting last.&quot;  However, I can see where it might not function properly on some customized UIs if said UI is set up to deal with the TAB save using the previous system.  So, at length, my advice would be to make sure you're running the most updated version of your UI if you're running something besides default.  I'm running the default UI, for the record.
<br />

<br />
3)  You mentioned clicking in your reply, and I know clicking can be generalized to mean any form of targeting, but I figured I should say this anyway:  when I use TAB to swap, I generally use autotarget and my MA hotkey to acquire the two critters in my targeting history.  You may want to experiment with targeting without ever clicking (as in target left-click) on a mob; perhaps there is a bug with click targeting and TAB.
<br />

<br />
4)  And btw, my TAB toggling was also broken for a time after the new system was implemented, but it spontaneously started working again after a patch one day.
<br />

<br />
I'm going to do a bit of experimenting tonight; if I find out anything concrete I'll post again.</span></td>
