				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm only a 57 bard but i have no problems at all pulling through doors and getting no adds.  I have done almost 100 adventures now and only 4 loss's due to 3 collects before they fixed them and 1 loss due to a player who zoned in with us then said he was finding another group before we killed anything.
<br />

<br />
What i do is walk up to the door and click on it from as far away as i can and back up.  You get use to the distance after awhile and dont think much about it.  The next thing i do is click F9 till i get to the second to the last view.  If you hold ALT and hit the up or down arrow it changes your camera height.  I usually adjust my camera angle to be level with the ground before i zone in or just after i zone in.
<br />

<br />
To keep things moving fast i leave one mob alive in the room we are curently in and move to the second room and lull away.  At lower lvls they would kill the mob about the time i got the room lulled for pulling.  But as i get higher and mobs have more hp's i stay and help them kill the mob till about 50% then i go and start lulling the next room.
<br />

<br />
Only a few times have i had adds and it comes from mobs either being stacked on top of each other or so close even lulled they agro each other.  The other way i have gotten a few adds is when a mob is standing infront of the door and either i pull or the puller pulls that mob before i have a chance to lull the guards on the other side.
<br />

<br />
To sum it up i just use F9 to get a better camera angle and use ALT + down arrow to get a ground level view and move my camera threw the door infront of me so i can see all the mobs that are standing beside the door.  Since our lull does not need a fov it works 99% of the time for me.
<br />

<br />
Silkworm</span></td>
